# Filter genes with very low counts
keep_genes <- rowSums(count_matrix >= 5) >= 2  # At least 2 samples must have count  5
filtered_counts <- count_matrix[keep_genes, ]

# Check dimensions after filtering
dim(filtered_counts)
## [1] 15369    10
# Convert raw counts to DGEList (for edgeR normalization)
dge <- DGEList(counts = filtered_counts)

# Calculate CPM
cpm_matrix <- cpm(dge, log = FALSE)  # If log=TRUE, it will log-transform

# Save normalized CPM matrix
write.csv(cpm_matrix, "normalized_cpm.csv")
# Log2 transform CPM (if required)
log_cpm_matrix <- log2(cpm_matrix + 1)

# Save log2-transformed CPM
write.csv(log_cpm_matrix, "normalized_log2_cpm.csv")
# Compute TPM (Transcripts Per Million)
tpm_matrix <- cpm(dge, log = FALSE) / rowSums(cpm(dge, log = FALSE)) * 1e6

# Save TPM matrix
write.csv(tpm_matrix, "normalized_tpm.csv")
# Define correct output directory
output_dir <- "C:/Users/dell/Downloads/Data_2/"

# Save existing matrices
write.csv(cpm_matrix, paste0(output_dir, "normalized_cpm.csv"))
write.csv(log_cpm_matrix, paste0(output_dir, "normalized_log2_cpm.csv"))
write.csv(tpm_matrix, paste0(output_dir, "normalized_tpm.csv"))
list.files("C:/Users/dell/Downloads/Data_2/Normalized_data", pattern = "*.csv")

Outputs:

Cell fractions are estimated for: B cells, Cytotoxic cells, Dendritic cells, Macrophages, Mast cells, etc. Differences between Normal and Tumor Samples: Macrophage levels are higher in tumor samples, which is expected due to immune infiltration in cancer. Cytotoxic cells show mixed trends across patients. Dendritic cell scores are higher in tumor samples, suggesting increased antigen presentation activity.

Finally generating the heatmap

# Generate a combined heatmap
Heatmap(
  as.matrix(combined_data),  # Convert to matrix
  name = "Proportions",
  column_title = "Combined Deconvolution Methods",
  cluster_columns = TRUE,
  cluster_rows = TRUE,
  show_row_dend = TRUE,
  row_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = 7),  # Reduce row font size
  column_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = 7),  # Reduce column font size
  column_names_rot = 90,  # Rotate column names to 90 degrees
  heatmap_legend_param = list(title = "Proportions", title_gp = gpar(fontsize = 9)),
  cell_fun = function(j, i, x, y, width, height, fill) {
    if (abs(combined_data[i, j]) > 3) {  # Highlight significant values
      grid.text(round(combined_data[i, j], 1), x, y, gp = gpar(fontsize = 5, col = "black"))
    }
  }
)

perform_t_tests <- function(data) {
  results <- data.frame(Cell_Type = rownames(data), p_value = NA)

  for (i in 1:nrow(data)) {
    normal_values <- as.numeric(data[i, grepl("Normal", colnames(data))])
    tumour_values <- as.numeric(data[i, grepl("Tumour", colnames(data))])

    normal_values <- normal_values[!is.na(normal_values)]
    tumour_values <- tumour_values[!is.na(tumour_values)]

    if (length(normal_values) >= 2 & length(tumour_values) >= 2) {
      t_test <- t.test(normal_values, tumour_values, var.equal = FALSE)
      results$p_value[i] <- t_test$p.value
    } else {
      results$p_value[i] <- NA
    }
  }

  # Filter significant results (p < 0.05)
  significant_results <- results[!is.na(results$p_value) & results$p_value < 0.05, ]
  
  return(significant_results)
}
epic_significant <- perform_t_tests(epic_data)
xcell_significant <- perform_t_tests(xcell_data)
consensus_significant <- perform_t_tests(consensus_data)

# Load required package
library(ggplot2)

# Function to create boxplots for significant cell types
plot_boxplots <- function(data, significant_cells, method_name) {
  for (cell in significant_cells$Cell_Type) {
    if (cell %in% rownames(data)) {
      plot_data <- data.frame(
        Value = c(as.numeric(data[cell, grepl("Normal", colnames(data))]),
                  as.numeric(data[cell, grepl("Tumour", colnames(data))])),
        Group = rep(c("Normal", "Tumour"), each = sum(grepl("Normal", colnames(data))))
      )

      p <- ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = Group, y = Value, fill = Group)) +
        geom_boxplot(alpha = 0.7) +
        ggtitle(paste(method_name, "-", cell)) +
        theme_minimal() +
        theme(legend.position = "none") +
        xlab("Group") + ylab("Cellular Estimate")

      print(p)  # Display the plot
    }
  }
}

# Generate boxplots for xCell and ConsensusTME (EPIC had no significant results)
plot_boxplots(xcell_data, xcell_significant, "xCell")

plot_boxplots(consensus_data, consensus_significant, "ConsensusTME")
